<h2>Step 5: Keep Content Fresh</h2>
<p>Content freshness is a stronger signal for Perplexity than for Google. 70% of top-cited sources were published or updated within the last 12 to 18 months, per <a href="https://llmclicks.ai/blog/perplexity-seo-reverse-engineering/">LLMClicks research</a>.</p>
<p>Perplexity applies an exponential time decay to content. A page published today gets maximum freshness weight. That weight drops sharply over weeks and months. By month 18, the freshness signal is near zero.</p>
<p><strong>Freshness strategy:</strong></p>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Action</th>
<th>Frequency</th>
<th>Impact</th>
</tr>
</thead>
